Response ID: resp_3258
Response Text: More organizations getting funding overall rather than a handful of orgs receiving $150,000 and others (who have served austin for decades and provided jobs for artists) receiving zero support. 

Same with elevate: rather than some orgs receiving $80,000 and others receiving $0, it should be more equally split amongst orgs that qualify so we don’t have to fold up shop while newer organizations who don’t have as much of a following yet are awarded amounts that most austin artists have never been awarded before. 

It feels like a clear message of “out with the old and in with the new” even when the older orgs are still trying to thrive and present exciting work for the community and are still providing valuable jobs to artists who are emerging and established.

